File handling in c:
File handling allow reading form and writing to files.

Type of files:
Text file: Store data in human- readable format.
Binary file: Store data in binary format.
File operations:
Opening a file:
FILE*file_pointer = fopen(“filename”,”mode”);

Modes:”r”(read),”w”(write),”a”(append).
Closing afile:
Writing mode;
fprintf(file_pointer,”Text”);
fputs(“Text”,file_pointer);
Reading mode:
fscanf(file_pointer,”format_specifier”,&variable);
fgets(buffer,size,file_pointer);
EOF- end of file.
Common preprocessor directives;
These are instructions executed before the actual compilation of code.
#include:used to define.
            Constants/macro.
#include:includes header files.

Conditional compilation:
MACRO: 
Command line: It allows passing information to a program when its start execution.

argc:argument count.
argv:array of string.
Syntax:
int main(int argc,char*argv[])
Error Handling:
Types:
Syntax error
Run time error
Logical error

Debugging:
Using printf
Using debuggers
while(ch=fgetc(ch!=EOF))

